curl -XPOST 'http://localhost:9200/electronic_products/_create/3899' -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{"product_name": "SGM3138", "table_name": "GENERAL DESCRIPTION", "content": "GENERAL DESCRIPTION  The SGM3138 is a current-regulated white LED driver  with integrated low dropout current sources and a high  efficiency charge pump. The charge pump has  automatically selectable 1×/1.5× fractional operation  modes. The SGM3138 is well suited for white LED  applications powered by a Li-Ion battery due to small  equivalent open-loop resistance in 1× mode.  The supply voltage operates from 2.7V to 5.5V. The  SGM3138 supports up to 6 LEDs for total maximum  120mA current. The LED reference current is set  through an internal resistor. The SGM3138 contains a  4-bit digital-to-analog converter for 16-step LED current  control. The LED current can be set between 1.25mA  and 20mA by a serial pulse input signal into the  EN/SET pin.  The SGM3138 provides less than 1μA shutdown  current and soft-start function. Built-in soft-start circuitry  avoids excessive inrush current during startup and  mode transition.  The SGM3138 is available in a Green TQFN-3×3-16L  package. It operates over an ambient temperature range  of -40℃ to +85℃.  "}'
curl -XPOST 'http://localhost:9200/electronic_products/_create/3900' -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{"product_name": "SGM3138", "table_name": "FEATURES", "content": "FEATURES  ● Input Voltage Range: 2.7V to 5.5V  ● Support to 6 LEDs at 20mA Each  ● 16-Step Brightness Control Through One-Wire  Interface  ● 1× and 1.5× Charge Pump for High Conversion  Efficiency  ● Switching Frequency: 1MHz  ● ±5% Regulated LED Current Matching  ● Built-in Soft-Start for Reducing Inrush Current   ● Low Input Ripple and Low EMI  ● Protection Features   Over-Current Protection   Under-Voltage Lockout   Thermal Shutdown  ● Operating Temperature Range: -40℃ to +85℃  ● Available in a Green TQFN-3×3-16L Package    "}'
